# Mouse
OnDesktop Mouse1 :HideMenus
OnDesktop Mouse2 :WorkspaceMenu
OnDesktop Mouse3 :RootMenu
OnDesktop Mouse4 :PrevWorkspace
OnDesktop Mouse5 :NextWorkspace

OnLeftGrip Move1 :StartResizing bottomleft
OnRightGrip Move1 :StartResizing bottomright

OnTitlebar Control Mouse1 :StartTabbing
OnTitlebar Double Mouse1 :Maximize
OnTitlebar Mouse5 :Shade
OnTitlebar Mouse4 :Unshade
OnTitlebar Mouse1 :MacroCmd {Raise} {Focus} {ActivateTab}
OnTitlebar Mouse2 :Lower
OnTitlebar Mouse3 :WindowMenu
OnTitlebar Move1  :StartMoving

OnToolbar Mouse4 :PrevWindow {static groups} (iconhidden=no)
OnToolbar Mouse5 :NextWindow {static groups} (iconhidden=no)

OnWindow Mod4 Mouse1 :MacroCmd {Raise} {Focus} {StartMoving}
OnWindow Mod4 Mouse2 :Close
OnWindow Mod4 Mouse3 :MacroCmd {Raise} {Focus} {StartResizing NearestCorner}

OnWindowBorder Move1 :StartMoving

# 
Mod1 Tab :NextWindow {groups} (workspace=[current])
Mod1 Shift Tab :PrevWindow {groups} (workspace=[current])

# cycle through tabs in the current window
Mod4 Tab :NextTab
Mod4 Shift Tab :PrevTab

# go to a specific tab in the current window
Mod4 1 :Tab 1
Mod4 2 :Tab 2
Mod4 3 :Tab 3
Mod4 4 :Tab 4
Mod4 5 :Tab 5
Mod4 6 :Tab 6
Mod4 7 :Tab 7
Mod4 8 :Tab 8
Mod4 9 :Tab 9

# open a terminal
Control Mod1 t :Exec x-terminal-emulator

# open a dialog to run programs
Mod1 F2 :Exec dmenu_run -fn "Monospace-12"

# volume settings, using common keycodes
# if these don't work, use xev to find out your real keycodes
XF86AudioRaiseVolume :Exec amixer sset Master 5%+
XF86AudioLowerVolume :Exec amixer sset Master 5%-
XF86AudioMute :Exec amixer sset Master toggle

# current window commands
Mod4 Q :Close
Mod4 Shift Q :Kill
Mod4 Down :Minimize
Mod4 Up :Maximize
Mod4 f :Fullscreen


# Menus
Mod1 space :WindowMenu
Control space :WorkspaceMenu
Mod4 space :RootMenu
Mod4 w :Exec rofi -show window

# exit fluxbox
Control Mod1 Delete :Exit

# change to previous/next workspace
Mod4 Left :PrevWorkspace
Mod4 Right :NextWorkspace

# send the current window to previous/next workspace
Mod4 Shift Left :SendToPrevWorkspace
Mod4 Shift Right :SendToNextWorkspace

# send the current window and follow it to previous/next workspace
Mod4 Control Left :TakeToPrevWorkspace
Mod4 Control Right :TakeToNextWorkspace

# change to a specific workspace
Mod4 F1 :Workspace 1
Mod4 F2 :Workspace 2
Mod4 F3 :Workspace 3
Mod4 F4 :Workspace 4
Mod4 F5 :Workspace 5
Mod4 F6 :Workspace 6
Mod4 F7 :Workspace 7
Mod4 F8 :Workspace 8
Mod4 F9 :Workspace 9
Mod4 F10 :Workspace 10
Mod4 F11 :Workspace 11
Mod4 F12 :Workspace 12

# send the current window to a specific workspace
Shift Mod4 F1 :SendToWorkspace 1
Shift Mod4 F2 :SendToWorkspace 2
Shift Mod4 F3 :SendToWorkspace 3
Shift Mod4 F4 :SendToWorkspace 4
Shift Mod4 F5 :SendToWorkspace 5
Shift Mod4 F6 :SendToWorkspace 6
Shift Mod4 F7 :SendToWorkspace 7
Shift Mod4 F8 :SendToWorkspace 8
Shift Mod4 F9 :SendToWorkspace 9
Shift Mod4 F10 :SendToWorkspace 10
Shift Mod4 F11 :SendToWorkspace 11
Shift Mod4 F12 :SendToWorkspace 12

# send the current window and change to a specific workspace
Control Shift Mod4 F1 :TakeToWorkspace 1
Control Shift Mod4 F2 :TakeToWorkspace 2
Control Shift Mod4 F3 :TakeToWorkspace 3
Control Shift Mod4 F4 :TakeToWorkspace 4
Control Shift Mod4 F5 :TakeToWorkspace 5
Control Shift Mod4 F6 :TakeToWorkspace 6
Control Shift Mod4 F7 :TakeToWorkspace 7
Control Shift Mod4 F8 :TakeToWorkspace 8
Control Shift Mod4 F9 :TakeToWorkspace 9
Control Shift Mod4 F10 :TakeToWorkspace 10
Control Shift Mod4 F11 :TakeToWorkspace 11
Control Shift Mod4 F12 :TakeToWorkspace 12

Print :Exec gnome-screenshot -aic
